                    </div>
                    <span>This book is an embarrassment to the Delphi community. That people like Ayres can even get published in the first place shows us how bad things really are. If I'd paid for this book out of my own pocket, I'd be sending it back, I promise you. Ayres can't write and has no knack for explaining anything. He does a disservice to Delphi and the few of us still building apps with it. <P>Now, please, someone - write a Win32 API book on Delphi that's worth reading, not something like this hackneyed gradeschool stuff.</span>
                  
              
